MTN Group, Remgro, Zeder Investments: South African Equity Market Preview

-- B y   S t e p h e n   G u n n i o n   a n d   S i k o n a t h i   M a n t s h a n t s h a
-- 
2011-06-21T22:00:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-21/mtn-remgro-zeder-investments-south-african-equities-preview.html
The following stocks may rise or
fall in  South Africa  today. Symbols are in parentheses and
prices are from the last close.  The FTSE/JSE Africa All Share Index rose 344.23, or 1.1
percent, to 30,971.88 at the 5 p.m. close in Johannesburg.  MTN Group Ltd. (MTN)  : Africa’s largest mobile-phone
operator holds a  shareholders’ meeting . The stock gained 65
cents, or 0.5 percent, to 136.80 rand.  Remgro Ltd. (REM)  : Earnings per share after one-time
items climbed 18 percent to 8.12 rand in the year through March,
from 6.90 rand a year earlier, the group said in a regulatory
statement. Remgro increased 1.39 rand, or 1.3 percent, to 110.59
rand.  Zeder Investments Ltd. (ZED)  : The agricultural
investment group has purchased shares in fruit exporter  Capespan
Group Ltd. , taking its shareholding in the company to 32.7
percent. Zeder has made a buyout offer for the company. The
stock advanced 1 cent, or 0.4 percent, to 2.38 rand.  To contact the reporters on this story:
